### Premium Module Purchase Flow Tests
### BASE_URL should be your API endpoint
@BASE_URL = http://localhost:8001
### AUTH_TOKEN should be a valid JWT from your login
@AUTH_TOKEN = your_jwt_token_here

### 1. List Available Modules
# Should return MASTER_COSTBOOK ($4,999), GOLDEN_PETL ($2,999), GOLDEN_BOM ($1,999)
GET {{BASE_URL}}/billing/modules/available
Authorization: Bearer {{AUTH_TOKEN}}

###

### 2. Check Module Access (before purchase)
# Should return hasAccess: false
GET {{BASE_URL}}/billing/modules/MASTER_COSTBOOK/check
Authorization: Bearer {{AUTH_TOKEN}}

###

### 3. Get Company's Active Modules
# Should return empty array (or list of purchased modules)
GET {{BASE_URL}}/billing/modules/company
Authorization: Bearer {{AUTH_TOKEN}}

###

### 4. Initiate Module Purchase
# Returns clientSecret for Stripe Elements
# Use this in your frontend with Stripe.js to confirm payment
POST {{BASE_URL}}/billing/modules/MASTER_COSTBOOK/purchase
Authorization: Bearer {{AUTH_TOKEN}}

###

### 5. Grant Module Access (DEV ONLY - bypasses Stripe)
# In production, this happens automatically via webhook after payment
POST {{BASE_URL}}/billing/modules/MASTER_COSTBOOK/grant
Authorization: Bearer {{AUTH_TOKEN}}

###

### 6. Verify Module Access (after purchase)
# Should return hasAccess: true
GET {{BASE_URL}}/billing/modules/MASTER_COSTBOOK/check
Authorization: Bearer {{AUTH_TOKEN}}

###

### Stripe Webhook (POST from Stripe servers)
# This is called automatically by Stripe after successful payment
# You can test locally with Stripe CLI:
#   stripe listen --forward-to localhost:8001/webhooks/stripe
#   stripe trigger payment_intent.succeeded

POST {{BASE_URL}}/webhooks/stripe
Content-Type: application/json
Stripe-Signature: your_stripe_signature

{
  "id": "evt_test_123",
  "type": "payment_intent.succeeded",
  "data": {
    "object": {
      "id": "pi_test_123",
      "amount": 499900,
      "currency": "usd",
      "customer": "cus_test_123",
      "metadata": {
        "type": "module_purchase",
        "nexusCompanyId": "cmm0sv0sw00037n7n83z71ln9",
        "moduleCode": "MASTER_COSTBOOK",
        "userId": "user_id_here"
      },
      "status": "succeeded"
    }
  }
}

###
